  30 Mar 2004; Chris Aniszczyk <zx@gentoo.org> jdom-1.0_beta9.ebuild,
  files/jdom-1.0_beta8-nojdk1.1.patch:
  Version bump

  18 Mar 2004; Chris Aniszczyk <zx@gentoo.org> jdom-1.0_beta8-r4.ebuild,
  jdom-1.0_beta9.ebuild:
  Clean up, stable on x86.

*jdom-1.0_beta9 (25 Jan 2004)

  25 Jan 2004; Adrian Almenar <strider@gentoo.org> jdom-1.0_beta8-r4.ebuild,
  jdom-1.0_beta9.ebuild:
  Marked stable on ppc,sparc, added new version to testing.
  Thanks to Chris Aniszczyk <zx@mea-culpa.net> for the update. Closes #37241.

*jdom-1.0_beta8-r4 (26 May 2003)

  26 May 2003; Dylan Carlson <absinthe@gentoo.org> jdom-1.0_beta8-r4.ebuild:
  In this version, ant.jar will not be installed. Also JDOM will DEPEND on xalan
  and xerces separately, and those JARs will not be installed either. So be sure
  to add those packages to your CLASSPATH via java-config if you want JDOM to
  function. Closes #20066.

*jdom-1.0_beta8-r3 (26 May 2003)

  26 May 2003; Dylan Carlson <absinthe@gentoo.org> jdom-1.0_beta8-r3.ebuild,
  files/jdom-1.0_beta8-nojdk1.1.patch:
  Version bump/fix to close bug #15731.  Thanks to Zhen Lin <lowzl@hotmail.com>.

*jdom-1.0_beta8-r2 (12 Jan 2003)

  12 Jan 2003; Matthew Kennedy <mkennedy@gentoo.org>
  jdom-1.0_beta8-r2.ebuild, ChangeLog,
  files/digest-jdom-1.0_beta8-r2 :

  Removes JDK 1.1 version of JDOM and supporting com.sun.collections.*
  JAR (resolves bug #13719)

*jdom-1.0_beta8-r1 (10 Jul 2002)

  01 Aug 2002; Karl Trygve Kalleberg <karltk@gentoo.org> jdom-1.0_beta8-r1.ebuild :
  
